[Example]
S13_MAINTAINER_REFERENCE: Maintainer quick reference

[Description]
| Name | Kind | Location | Purpose | Notes |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `__main__` | entry point | `agents/s20_comprehensive.py:2034` | Starts the interactive CLI and cron autorun thread. | Owns `history` initialization and quit handling. |
| `agent_loop` | function | `agents/s20_comprehensive.py:1901` | Orchestrates model calls, tool execution, compaction, and stop conditions. | Main change-impact hotspot. |
| `cron_autorun_loop` | function | `agents/s20_comprehensive.py:2017` | Injects scheduled prompts and enters `agent_loop` under `agent_lock`. | Shares history with CLI path. |
| `Task` | dataclass | `agents/s20_comprehensive.py:78` | Represents `.tasks/task_*.json` records. | Update with transition logic. |
| `create_task` / `claim_task` / `complete_task` | functions | `agents/s20_comprehensive.py:93` | Create, claim, and complete task state. | `claim_task` enforces dependencies. |
| `validate_worktree_name` | function | `agents/s20_comprehensive.py:180` | Validates worktree path names. | First boundary before git sees a name. |
| `create_worktree` / `remove_worktree` | functions | `agents/s20_comprehensive.py:209` | Manage git worktrees and task binding. | Removal checks local changes unless forced. |
| `scan_skills` / `assemble_system_prompt` | functions | `agents/s20_comprehensive.py:302` | Build skill registry and system prompt. | Prompt includes memories, MCP, and teammates. |
| `safe_path` / `run_bash` / file tools | functions | `agents/s20_comprehensive.py:378` | Execute local tools and enforce file path boundaries. | Bash remains broad and relies on hook policy. |
| `MessageBus` / `ProtocolState` | class/dataclass | `agents/s20_comprehensive.py:479` | Provide mailbox messaging and request state. | Inbox reads delete files. |
| `spawn_teammate_thread` | function | `agents/s20_comprehensive.py:605` | Runs autonomous teammate model loop. | Contains plan approval gate. |
| `permission_hook` | function | `agents/s20_comprehensive.py:879` | Gates risky tool_use blocks before execution. | String matching is teaching-grade. |
| `spawn_subagent` | function | `agents/s20_comprehensive.py:1004` | Runs synchronous subagent loop. | Uses `SUB_TOOLS` and shared hooks. |
| `compact_history` / `reactive_compact` | functions | `agents/s20_comprehensive.py:1133` | Summarize or recover oversized context. | Writes transcripts. |
| `with_retry` | function | `agents/s20_comprehensive.py:1167` | Retries API calls and switches fallback model for overload. | State is per loop invocation. |
| `start_background_task` / `collect_background_results` | functions | `agents/s20_comprehensive.py:1230` | Run slow tool work asynchronously and inject notifications. | Results arrive later, not in the original tool result. |
| `CronJob` / `schedule_job` | dataclass/function | `agents/s20_comprehensive.py:1282` | Represent and persist scheduled prompts. | Cron parser is intentionally simple. |
| `MCPClient` / `connect_mcp` / `assemble_tool_pool` | class/functions | `agents/s20_comprehensive.py:1480` | Mock MCP discovery and dynamic tool merging. | Tool names become `mcp__server__tool`. |
| `BUILTIN_TOOLS` / `BUILTIN_HANDLERS` | tables | `agents/s20_comprehensive.py:1670` | Map model-visible schemas to local handlers. | Additions must keep schema, handler, and permission policy aligned. |

[UML]
None

[Detail]
| Change Type | Check These Locations | Reason |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Add a builtin tool | `BUILTIN_TOOLS`, `BUILTIN_HANDLERS`, `permission_hook` | Schema, handler, and safety policy must stay aligned. |
| Add an MCP server | `MOCK_SERVERS`, `connect_mcp`, `assemble_tool_pool` | Tool names are normalized and prefixed. |
| Change task status values | `Task`, `claim_task`, `complete_task`, `scan_unclaimed_tasks` | State transitions and auto-claim logic must agree. |
| Change teammate protocol | `MessageBus`, `ProtocolState`, `spawn_teammate_thread`, `run_review_plan` | Request-id matching and waiting gates define correctness. |
| Change context budgeting | `prepare_context`, `tool_result_budget`, `micro_compact`, `compact_history` | These functions mutate `messages` in place. |
| Change long-running tool behavior | `should_run_background`, `start_background_task`, `collect_background_results` | Background results are delivered on a later turn. |
| Change the main loop | `agent_loop`, `call_llm`, `with_retry`, `trigger_hooks` | Every tool_use block needs clear feedback or a clear exit path. |
